<AUTHOR>kenister</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>Coolers, storage, performance. And I wouldn't dare forget about comfort. I bought got the SLT fully loaded. I couldnt break the back end loose. I couldnt get the tires to lock. This truck is amazing. I am, well used to be a Chevy guy through and through, but this? Good job Dodge. It has the highest power/weight ratio out of all the trucks. I did the math and took it to the street. It feels like a truck sticks like velcro and is fun on the street. Haven't got the chance to go offraod, but can't wait. Took a big train track bump, at 85 mph, didnt feel a thing. Oh and by the way I got an SLT with the 5.7 hemi and the offraod package. It can be done.</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Acceleration, got the 3.95 rd and love it. It's got so much power, and 22.68 mpg? Almost too good to be true. The seats, and cup holders are everywhere! Remote start, I can start it from my bedroom when I get up for work then it's already warmed up!</FAVORITE>
